'''Tekshar Falls''' was a five-hundred-[[Meter/Legends|meter]] high, man-made [[Water/Legends|waterfall]] located on the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core World]] of [[Kuat/Legends|Kuat]]. Created at great [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|expense]] by diverting a natural river through the entertainment center of [[Kuat City]], the [[Planet/Legends|planetary]] [[Capital/Legends|capital]], the Tekshar Falls became something of an extravagant water feature for the eponymously named [[Tekshar Falls Casino]] that was built within its cascading waters. The waterfall provided the [[Casino/Legends|casino]] with [[Hydroelectric power generator|hydroelectric power]] independent of Kuat [[City/Legends|City's]] power grid, and automated [[Force field/Legends|force fields]] prevented any water from reaching the casino itself. To reach the casino entrance, [[gambler]]s were required to pass through a stretch of the Tekshar Falls, which would part upon detecting incoming guests via a [[Motion sensor/Legends|motion sensor]].<ref name="Sacrifice" />

==Behind the scenes==
Tekshar Falls was first introduced to the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe in the novel [[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice|''Sacrifice'']], the fifth entry in the multi-[[Author/Legends|author]] ''[[Star Wars: Legacy of the Force]]'' series, written by [[Karen Traviss]] and published [[May 29]], [[2007]].<ref name="Sacrifice" />

